'''Earthworks''' is a professional [[audio engineering|audio equipment]] company founded by [[David E. Blackmer]] in the mid 1990s after he left [[dbx, Inc.|dbx]] to design studio [[microphone]]s, [[preamplifier]]s and studio reference [[Loudspeaker|monitors]].

Their products are based on Blackmer's research into [[ultrasound|ultrasonic frequencies]] in [[sound reproduction]] and his claims that the time resolution of human hearing is 5 microseconds or better - corresponding to 200&nbsp;kHz, well above the 20&nbsp;kHz conventionally accepted as the limit of human [[hearing (sense)|hearing]].

